ve and breathe it every day.","Incapsula and Radware provide DDoS protection services available for outsourcing. For the most part, they match features and capabilities. In terms of setup and management, both provide you with an online portal and real-time monitoring. Both allow you to enable their attack mitigation services with a simple DNS change. And both provide BGP-based redirection services. DNS and BGP are both efficient redirection methods. DNS is easier and faster to deploy. However, if you have a complex infrastructure with many hosts and a C Class IP range, BGP might be the better way. Of course the DNS-versus-BGP decision involves pluses and minuses that cannot be tallied except by you as you examine exactly what trade-offs are best indicated for your exact situation. If the decision is to redirect with DNS or BGP, Incapsula and Radware can both handle either one. The strong similarities between Incapsula and Radware extend to help and support. Both operate 24/7 security operations centers that you can reach at any hour on any day via live chat, telephone or email.","Incapsula and Radware have equivalent mitigation capabilities. Both services avail themselves of Webroot&#39;s IP Reputation service to stop known bad traffic at the edge of the network. Both are PCI compliant, so if you are hosting an eCommerce site, your credit card provider will not fine you because of your DDoS service. The difference between the two companies is that Incapsula&#39;s service is completely cloud based. You make a DNS change and your traffic starts redirecting via Incapsula&#39;s network. Incapsula grooms your traffic before passing it back to you. Radware&#39;s service is mostly cloud based. However, there is one component that Radware requires you to deploy locally to prevent Layer 7 application attacks. Once Incapsula and Radware accept responsibility for shielding your traffic from DDoS attacks, they match each other feature for feature. Their network infrastructures follow different models, however. Incapsula owns and controls 15 scrubbing centers to condition client traffic. Radware equips ISPs with anti-DDoS technology and Radware&#39;s DefensePipe service extends its premise-based protections to multiple scrubbing centers.","In summary, Incapsula&#39;s DNS-based DDoS protection service lends itself to being able to provide protection within minutes, even if you don&#39;t contact Incapsula until you are actually under attack. In fact, if you have sufficient in-house expertise, Incapsula offers a self-service mode so that you never even need to talk to someone at Incapsula. When you sign up online, its system will send you a guide to walk you through the actions you need to perform to redirect your traffic through Incapsula. The decision to go with Radware rather than Incapsula would be more of a strategic decision because you would need at least as much time as it takes to deploy a piece of its equipment at your site."]},"id":"a25d3754-1adb-4b92-ac82-9c69dd26967a","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"article_page_7919","url":"/incapsula-and-radware-compared","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"randall-sutherland","url":"/author/randall-sutherland","dateCreated":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","name":"Randall Sutherland","dateModified":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","id":"9vN6VRi7r7TmwKJt8Zd5aP","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2013-06-06T13:17:03Z","datePublished":"2013-06-06T13:17:03Z","name":"Incapsula and Radware, Compared","synopsis":"At the enterprise level of information technology, there are at least three basic strategies emerging to counter denial of service attacks.","review":{},"strapline":"At the enterprise level of information technology, there are at least three basic strategies emerging to counter denial of service attacks.","language":"en","dateModified":"2015-08-17T14:08:36Z","id":"ZvCyDCWhXbuXLUooFHHaDA","meta":{"title":"Incapsula and Radware, Compared","desc